<target_code>
Here is the code of OS_SetLocalTime_Impl:
```c
int32 OS_SetLocalTime_Impl(const OS_time_t *time_struct)
{
    int             Status;
    int32           ReturnCode;
    struct timespec TimeSp;

    TimeSp.tv_sec  = OS_TimeGetTotalSeconds(*time_struct);
    TimeSp.tv_nsec = OS_TimeGetNanosecondsPart(*time_struct);

    Status = clock_settime(OSAL_GETTIME_SOURCE_CLOCK, &TimeSp);

    if (Status == 0)
    {
        ReturnCode = OS_SUCCESS;
    }
    else
    {
        ReturnCode = OS_ERROR;
    }

    return ReturnCode;
}
```
</target_code>
<additional code>Here are the definitions of symbols that are related to the target function OS_SetLocalTime_Impl:
static inline int64 OS_TimeGetTotalSeconds(OS_time_t tm)
{
    return (tm.ticks / OS_TIME_TICKS_PER_SECOND);
}
...
static inline uint32 OS_TimeGetNanosecondsPart(OS_time_t tm)
{
    return (uint32)OS_TimeGetFractionalPart(tm) * OS_TIME_TICK_RESOLUTION_NS;
}
...
#define OSAL_GETTIME_SOURCE_CLOCK CLOCK_REALTIME
...
typedef struct
{
    int64 ticks; /**< Ticks elapsed since reference point */
} OS_time_t
</additional code>
Please find suspicious code fragments in the code and report them. Other agents can not investigate other fragments that you do not report, so it is very important to find all suspicious fragments without missing any. Report the suspicious fragments AS MUCH AS POSSIBLE.
explanation: No occurrence of the C library function memcmp or any string comparison of null-terminated strings is present in the provided target or additional code. The function OS_SetLocalTime_Impl only computes integer tick/second and nanosecond values, fills a struct timespec, and calls clock_settime. The additional symbols/macros (OS_TimeGetTotalSeconds, OS_TimeGetNanosecondsPart, OSAL_GETTIME_SOURCE_CLOCK, and the OS_time_t typedef) operate on integer tick values or map to clock constants; none perform or wrap memcmp calls or manipulate C strings. Therefore Rule 21.14 (memcmp shall not be used to compare null terminated strings) does not apply to any fragment of the provided code.
